<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="73" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pacheco</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States in Guatemala and Honduras</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-09"><hi rend="italic">September
                                    9, 1891</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Pacheco states that the allusion of Salvadorian minister was evidently in
                        general terms that the Salvadorian Government would indemnify any vessel
                        that might be unjustly and exceptionally detained in Salvadorian ports.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>